abstract: Economic sanctions that blocked bond payments have strengthened efforts to seal off Moscow from global markets.
snippet: Economic sanctions that blocked bond payments have strengthened efforts to seal off Moscow from global markets.
lead_paragraph: Russia missed a deadline for making bond payments on Sunday, a move signaling its first default on international debt in more than a century, after Western sanctions thwarted the government’s efforts to pay foreign investors. The lapse adds to efforts to seal Moscow off from global capital markets for years.

main: Russia Misses Bond Deadline, Signaling Its First Default on Foreign Debt Since 1918
print_headline: Russia Edges To the Brink Of a Default

abstract: Tom McCoy's Sunday puzzle might be hard to get a handle on, but it’s worth it!
snippet: Tom McCoy's Sunday puzzle might be hard to get a handle on, but it’s worth it!
lead_paragraph: SUNDAY PUZZLE — This grid marks the Sunday return of Tom McCoy after a far-too-long absence — nearly two years — that likely corresponds to a period of intense study. Mr. McCoy, who lives in Wexford, Pa., recently defended his doctoral dissertation in cognitive science at Johns Hopkins University, on the subject of how language is represented in artificial intelligence systems and what that tells us about language in humans. This fall, he will begin a postdoctoral program at Princeton, which might be easier to juggle with crossword construction (probably wishful thinking on my part).

abstract: We need to start treating the protective end of the intelligence process like it’s as important as the collection part.
snippet: We need to start treating the protective end of the intelligence process like it’s as important as the collection part.
lead_paragraph: America’s secrets aren’t sufficiently protected. The recent posting of apparently classified government documents to internet chat rooms allegedly by the Air National Guardsman Jack Teixeira reminds us that intelligence reporting is subject to a dilemma: Either we clamp down to prevent leaks, or we share information broadly within government to prevent harm to our nation and our troops.

main: I Was General Counsel of the N.S.A. America Has a Problem With Secrets.

abstract: Ukraine has charged four members of Russia’s National Guard with war crimes in Kherson. The four acted with such impunity, the authorities say, they did not mask their identities.
snippet: Ukraine has charged four members of Russia’s National Guard with war crimes in Kherson. The four acted with such impunity, the authorities say, they did not mask their identities.
lead_paragraph: They beat prisoners relentlessly and tortured them with electric shocks, waterboarding and mock executions. Three people died in their custody. Yet such was their sense of impunity, the Russians who seized control of a detention center in southern Ukraine last year and filled it with 200 detainees were careless about concealing their identities.

main: Shocks, Beatings, Mock Executions: Inside Kherson’s Detention Centers
print_headline: Shocks, Beatings and Mock Executions in Kherson
